Hey y’all. During the rebuilding of my teams old demo bot, I switched out it’s old Talon motor controllers with the newer Talon SRX controllers. After powering and test driving the bot, we realized that the motors were only getting 6 volts of power.

Here is the current situation:

  • PDP pushing the correct 12v to the input of the motor controllers.
  • Talon’s have been updated to latest firmware, and are running off of the CAN.
  • Talon’s have been calibrated, increasing their output by a whopping 0.2 volts. Subsequent calibration has done nothing.
  • Motor work fine when hooked to another power source.
  • Talon’s status lights are displaying normal, no error codes.
  • Changing the code values has not resulted in anything, all motors still run at the same voltage.
  • Battery has been swapped multiple times, no significant change in volts going to the Talons.

I’m pretty out of ideas at this point. My best guess is something with the code, but the programers swear up, down and sideways that the code is fine.
